certain type and level by straight DDing, then went after them with 3 elementals at a time.  Of course, the EEs do get an advantage in melee with more than one attacker, so they likely wouldn't do quite this much if singletons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugrolmn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grolmn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/15/02 3:37:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=258.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ice Pets in RvR</span><hr size=1> A theurgist on the Gawaine board was saying so.  I didn't know  if he was making it up or not.  Mainly posted here to get confirmation.  I can't decide whether to try to get to ice pet level at later stages of the game and this would sway my decision.  Right now I am leaning towards an earth/air combo with very little in ice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showPrevMessage?topicID=258.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showNextMessage?topicID=258.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=258.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.execpc.com/~msippel/thedruidsgrove/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.emailToFriend?topicID=258.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruids